$$A = \begin{bmatrix}5 & 9 \\      5 & 10  \end{bmatrix}

x = \begin{bmatrix}x0  \\      x1\end{bmatrix}

b = \begin{bmatrix}117  \\      125\end{bmatrix}$$

## Find matrix M, such that M A is a diagonal matrix

$$MA = \begin{bmatrix}      10 & -9 \\      -5 & 5  \end{bmatrix}
⋅\begin{bmatrix}5 & 9 \\      5 & 10  \end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}      5 & 0 \\      0 & 5  \end{bmatrix}$$

## Use M to find x in the equation Ax = b-

$$\begin{bmatrix}      10 & -9 \\      -5 & 5  \end{bmatrix}
⋅\begin{bmatrix}      x0 \\      x1 \end{bmatrix}
x = \begin{bmatrix}5x0 \\      5x1 \end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}      45 \\      40  \end{bmatrix}
$$

