# Question 6

![Question6.PNG](CS1MA20%20Autumn%20Assignment%202021%200f80efbfaa9643558303acc4580b397d/Question6.png)

## Find the determinant of A {1}

$$det\left(A\right)=10⋅8\ – 9⋅1 = 71$$

$$Determinant of A = 71$$

## Then find the inverse of A {2}

$$inv\left(A\right)=\left[\begin{matrix}8&-1\\-9&10\\\end{matrix}\right]⋅ \frac{1}{71}=\ \left[\begin{matrix}\frac{8}{71}&\frac{-1}{71}\\\frac{-1}{71}&\frac{10}{71}\\\end{matrix}\right]=\ \left[\begin{matrix}0.1127&-0.0141\\-0.1269&0.1408\\\end{matrix}\right]$$

$$Inverse of A=\left[\begin{matrix}\mathbf{0}.\mathbf{1127}&-\mathbf{0}.\mathbf{0141}\\-\mathbf{0}.\mathbf{1269}&\mathbf{0}.\mathbf{1408}\\\end{matrix}\right]$$

## Hence find x in the equation Ax = b {2}

$$\left[\begin{matrix}0.1127&-0.0141\\-0.1269&0.1408\\\end{matrix}\right]⋅\left[\begin{matrix}10&1\\9&8\\\end{matrix}\right]⋅\left[\begin{matrix}x0\\x1\\\end{matrix}\right]=\ \left[\begin{matrix}0.1127&-0.0141\\-0.1269&0.1408\\\end{matrix}\right]⋅\left[\begin{matrix}110\\170\\\end{matrix}\right]$$

$$\left[\begin{matrix}0.1127&-0.0141\\-0.1269&0.1408\\\end{matrix}\right]⋅\left[\begin{matrix}110\\170\\\end{matrix}\right]=\left[\begin{matrix}10\\10\\\end{matrix}\right];\ \ \mathbf{x}=\left[\begin{matrix}\mathbf{10}\\\mathbf{10}\\\end{matrix}\right]$$

$$Ax = b = \left[\begin{matrix}10&1\\9&8\\\end{matrix}\right]⋅\left[\begin{matrix}10\\10\\\end{matrix}\right]=\left[\begin{matrix}110\\170\\\end{matrix}\right]$$

## Then, use MATLAB to confirm your answer is correct {1}

