## By hand, use Cramer's Rule to find x {3}

$$det(A) =  \left[\begin{matrix}9&8\\10&9\\\end{matrix}\right]= 9⋅9 - 10⋅ 8 \\=81 -80=1$$

$$det(A) =  \left[\begin{matrix}9&8\\10&9\\\end{matrix}\right]= 9⋅9 - 10 ⋅ 8 \\=81 -80=1 \\D = 1$$

$$det(x0) =  \left[\begin{matrix}162&8\\181&9\\\end{matrix}\right]= 162⋅9 - 181 ⋅ 8 =10$$

$$det(x1) =  \left[\begin{matrix}9&162\\10&181\\\end{matrix}\right]= 9 ⋅ 181 - 10 ⋅ 162 =9$$

$$x1 = \frac{Dx1}{D} = \frac{9}{1} = 9$$

$$Ax = b = \left[\begin{matrix}9&8\\10&9\\\end{matrix}\right]⋅ \left[\begin{matrix}10\\9\\\end{matrix}\right]=\left[\begin{matrix}162\\181\\\end{matrix}\right]$$

